What are some cool projects to self host on a home Raspberry Pi (64 bit) Kubernetes cluster (Helm charts). arm64 support is a must. A lot of projects only build amd64 Docker containers which don&#x27;t run on my cluster.<p>I currently run:<p><pre><code>   - obenebs (provides abstraction for using local k8s worker disks as PVCs when running on-prem) -- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;openebs.io&#x2F;
   - metalLB (provides load balancer abstraction when running k8s on-prem) -- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;metallb.universe.tf&#x2F;
   - traefik (load balancer) -- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;traefik.io&#x2F;
   - minio (object storage s3 compliant) -- https:&#x2F;&#x2F;min.io&#x2F;
</code></pre>
Any other cool utilities or projects to play around with?
